attributes.Long form description:
The instructor asks the student to disassemble the piece of furniture. 
The student starts with the bottom shelf of the furniture, unscrewing one of the four hex socket head on the four legs. He removes the bottom shelf and places it on the table. Flips the furniture and starts unscrewing the hex socket head of the first leg of the upper shelf of the furniture. Flips the furniture again on its legs, unscrews the first leg, and place it on the table. Starts to unscrew the second leg of the furniture, removes it from the shelf, and place it on the table with the shelf. Lays the furniture on the table, unscrew the third furniture leg, and places it next to the others. Places the furniture upside down on the table to unscrew the last table leg and places it with the others. Turns the shelf upside down on the table. The instructor tells him that he can stop the recording.
